  "text": "The JVM bytecode interpreter implementation spans shared (platform-independent) and per-CPU-architecture files. The core dispatch loop and dispatch table live in templateInterpreter.cpp (DispatchTable class, _active_table/_normal_table). Template generation orchestration is in templateInterpreterGenerator.cpp (generate_all \u2192 set_entry_points_for_all_bytes, method_entry macro for each entry point kind). The bytecode template definitions and platform-independent helpers are in templateTable.cpp. Each CPU architecture provides its own templateTable_<arch>.cpp (per-bytecode code generation with dispatch_next/dispatch_base) and templateInterpreterGenerator_<arch>.cpp (generate_normal_entry, generate_method_entry, dispatch mechanics). The Zero interpreter (C++ fallback, no JIT) uses bytecodeInterpreter.cpp with a computed-goto/switch dispatch loop and zeroInterpreterGenerator.cpp for method entry setup. abstractInterpreter.cpp provides shared initialization.",
